 AP880318-0051 AP-NR-03-18-88 0527EST u i PM-SolarEclipse 03-18 0718 PM-Solar Eclipse,0741 Thousands Mark Total Eclipse With Prayers, Dancing and Drum-Beating By YASMIN ARQUIZA Associated Press Writer GENERAL SANTOS CITY, Philippines (AP) Thousands of peole prayed, cheered, danced, beat drums and observed other traditions today as a total eclipse of the sun darkened a wide area of Indonesia and the southern Philippines.
 The sun was blacked out by the shadow of the moon for up to four minutes along a 108-mile swath that moved from the Indian Ocean across Indonesia and the southern Philippine island of Mindanao.
